Got it — you want the **PHP cURL** version of the working Postman request.

Two things first:

1) The cURL you pasted **doesn’t include any query params**, so it’s not enough to generate the correct PHP request yet (pricing depends on params like `fields`, `priceType`, `company`, etc.).
2) Please **don’t paste full Bearer tokens**. I’ll show it as `{{TOKEN}}`.

If you tell me the exact params you used in Postman (or paste the full request URL with `?...`), I’ll tailor it precisely. In the meantime, here’s the correct PHP cURL template for WheelPros **Products Search** that includes all the common pricing-related params (including `sku=AB109-24128744N`):

```php
<?php

$token = getenv('WHEELPROS_TOKEN'); // or paste your token here temporarily
if (!$token) $token = '{{TOKEN}}';

$baseUrl = 'https://api.wheelpros.com/products/v1/search/wheel';

$params = [
  'page' => 1,
  'pageSize' => 10,

  // Pricing-related:
  'fields' => 'inventory,price',
  'priceType' => 'msrp',
  'company' => '1500',
  'currencyCode' => 'USD',

  // Optional (service accounts):
  'customer' => '1022896',

  // Helpful for reproducing your example:
  'sku' => 'AB109-24128744N',

  // Optional filters you might also have set:
  // 'availabilityType' => 'AVAILABLE',
  // 'realTimeInventory' => 'false',
];

$url = $baseUrl . '?' . http_build_query($params);

$ch = curl_init($url);
curl_setopt_array($ch, [
  CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER => true,
  CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER => [
    'Authorization: Bearer ' . $token,
    'Accept: application/json',
  ],
  CURLOPT_TIMEOUT => 30,
]);

$response = curl_exec($ch);
$httpCode = curl_getinfo($ch, CURLINFO_HTTP_CODE);

if ($response === false) {
  throw new Exception('cURL error: ' . curl_error($ch));
}

curl_close($ch);

echo "HTTP $httpCode\n";
echo $response . "\n";
```

